cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

The paper proposes a sequence-to-sequence neural attention network system for automatic text correction and completion, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also extensively uses deep learning techniques such as Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) and Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of deploying industrial scale deep neural network (DNN) models on devices with memory and processor resource constraints, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also presents a novel dataset and reports baseline performance for neural keyboard decoders, which are topics commonly discussed in the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
